sub_title: Founder and CEO at Samarali B.V
summary:
I have completed an MBA with 7 years of professional and international experience in various industries: FMCG, banking, retail, oil and gas and worked in US, Uzbekistan and the Netherlands. 

I am an ambitious and highly motivated individual with a proven track record of successfully accomplished highly complex assignments. In my career so far, I have been responsible for managing projects with complex stakeholder structure, building & managing global teams. Also, I’ve built international relationships with top profile banks across the globe eg. USA, Russia, China, Germany and Austria which allowed to save costs and attract international financing for private and public sector.  

My main areas of expertise are building international relations, Agile/Scrum, capital projects, finance, infrastructure, and stakeholder management. At my spare time I enjoy running, cycling and swimming and do/learn a lot about e-commerce/digital marketing.  I speak 4 languages - Russian (fluent), English (fluent), Uzbek (fluent) and my Dutch (intermediate) is improving fast.
